  "content": "# delete nodes with DELETE_NODE not DELETE_FILE\n\nWhen removing files or folders from a drive:\n\n```typescript\n// \u2705 Correct operation name\n{ type: \"DELETE_NODE\", scope: \"global\", input: { id: nodeId } }\n\n// \u274c This operation does not exist\n{ type: \"DELETE_FILE\", scope: \"global\", input: { id: nodeId } }\n```\n\nThe drive uses a node abstraction \u2014 both files and folders are \"nodes.\" The operation to remove either is `DELETE_NODE`. Since [[always check document model schema before calling addActions]], checking the drive schema first would reveal the correct operation name.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[mcp workflows]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
